cs.CC, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with complexity theory, specifically with separations between complexity classes and oracle results. This suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves communication complexity and information theory, which could place it in cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of amplification theorems and the analysis of algorithms suggest that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories.
